## 1.3. Reduction Excess Accumulation
To track energy dissipation, we introduce the local reduction excess variable e_n:
e_n = k_n - 1
If k_n = 1 (the baseline absolute minimum reduction), then e_n = 0. This represents a pure computational expansion step. If k_n >= 2, then e_n >= 1. This implies an active energy discharge phase, counteracting previous growth vectors. The cumulative excess parameter over a window of N iterations equals E_N = sum(e_n) from n = 1 to N.
